File: Eskom has implemented load reduction in six provinces. The power utility says it's trying to prevent network overloading in high-density areas. Flickr.com/Jalal Hameed Bhatti JOHANNESBURG - Eskom has implemented load reduction in six provinces. The localised power cuts will continue until 10pm in Gauteng, North West and the Free State. READ: SA's electricity crisis | Eskom names and shames defaulters Power outages are expected to last until 9pm in KwaZulu-Natal and the Eastern Cape, and until 9pm in the Northern Cape. The power utility says it's trying to prevent network overloading in high-density areas. It's also urging consumers to use electricity sparingly. Eskom Load Reduction Notice
